## Key learnings

- The .codex files are compiled to C# by the reference compiler. The codex
  build step runs `Codex.Cli build .` which reads codex.project.json.
- The generated C# class is Codex_Codex_Codex with all functions as static
  methods. Hyphens become underscores.
- CCE encoding: C# test code constructing IR must use CCE-encoded strings.
  "main" = "\u001a\u000f\u0011\u0012". The _Cce class is internal.
- No comments in Codex. Ever. Prose is the explanation layer.
- Avoid inline if/then/else in arithmetic — the emitter drops parens and
  breaks the fixed point. Use let bindings instead.
- Break large ++ chains and deeply nested lets into smaller named functions
  to reduce self-compilation time and type-checker pressure.
- The out/ directory must not contain .codex files when running codex build,
  or they get picked up by the **/*.codex glob and cause duplicate defs.
- Bare-metal memory is now 128MB (64 pages). HWM is 73MB.
